Subject: [PATCH 28/28] Remove ElevenLabs from skills, the /interview voice
 template and the release README

Upstream issue: (pai-nix — sovereignty policy; no upstream issue.)

Part 3/3 of the vendor-TTS removal (0026 = runtime, 0027 = installer).
Skills are executable instructions for the model — a skill that teaches
"call the vendor TTS API with ELEVENLABS_API_KEY" is functionality, not
prose, and after 0026/0027 it could only ever fail.

What changes:

  - skills/Remotion — Tools/Ref-elevenlabs-captions.md DELETED (pure
    vendor recipe); the TTS/STT steps in Tools/Ref-ai-pipeline.md and
    Workflows/GeneratedContentVideo.md become local-first placeholders
    (manual/local narration + local Whisper captions via AudioEditor)
    until the local TTS engine lands; SKILL.md description de-vendored;
    dangling pointers to the deleted file removed.
  - skills/Agents — voice registry comments in Data/Traits.yaml
    re-documented as legacy opaque ids (ids themselves stay — they are
    composition data the local engine maps or ignores);
    AgentPersonalities.md, SKILL.md, CUSTOMAGENTTEMPLATE.md de-vendored.
  - skills/Prompting — VoicePresets.yaml defaults de-vendored (model:
    none — the vendor model id is meaningless here); Voice.hbs label.
  - PAI/TOOLS/DAInterview.ts — the /interview tool's embedded YAML
    template wrote "provider: elevenlabs" into the user's voice config;
    now "provider: none" until the local engine registers its own.
  - README.md (release root) — after 0027 the README was WRONG: it
    promised the wizard "prompts for your ElevenLabs API key". First-run
    copy now tells the truth: voice arrives via a local TTS engine;
    the vendor-key prerequisite bullet is gone.

Verified: anchor-checked substitutions (count-guarded); rg -i
'elevenlabs|xi-api' clean across skills/ and README.md; zero dangling
references to the deleted reference file; both touched YAML files still
parse; whole series applies cleanly and nix build succeeds.

Known residual (deliberate, inert): DOCUMENTATION/*.md prose,
PAI-Install/README.md prose, skills/Art YouTube thumbnail example
SPECIFICATIONS.md (describes a vendor logo visible in an example
screenshot), Observability finances demo page + minified chunk.
